pageContext.claim: “Look, right now, I guess we're at 26 deaths, and if you look at the flu -- the flu, for this year -- we're at 8 mil- -- we're looking at 8,000 deaths. And, you know, hundreds of thousands of cases, but we have 8,000 deaths. So you have 8,000 versus 26 deaths, at this time.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump made a false comparison between a count for flu-related deaths, based on estimates of excess mortality, and the lab-confirmed deaths for covid-18.
